      "content": "This is a very common experience, as your monthly payment is calculated to cover the highest interest payment possible in the first year of your loan. During this period, the bulk of your payment goes toward interest, so the principal balance decreases very slowly. Over time, as your balance drops, the interest portion of your payment decreases, meaning more of your fixed payment goes toward paying down the principal, which speeds up the payoff process.",
